				<p>Around about the time we finished making Make It: Technobabble, we were thinking "What other cool things can we make with this codebase?" At a similar time, a BBC R+D team pitched an idea at Connected Studios to make a music visualiser creator which would inspire Digital Creativity in the yoot. These two things combined, along with super cool art from people like <a href="http://news.richt-what.co.uk/">RichT</a>, <a href="https://www.behance.net/adoraattack">Adora Attacks</a>, Melbs, Peskimo, Ciaran O'Connor and more, and made Vizii. We built them to be easily converted to different brands, so along with BBC Introducing one, there is also a <a href="https://www.mixital.co.uk/channel/wordcraft-vizii">Poetry version</a>, and <a href="https://www.mixital.co.uk/channel/ten-pieces-vizii">Classical version</a>.</p>


